Title: FUTURE DIRECTIONS FOR HUMAN-COMPUTER INTERACTION  
Author: BEN SHNEIDERMAN 
Address: College Park, MD 20742, USA  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science, University of Maryland,  
Abstract: This paper offers a set of goals for user interface development and then scenarios of future developments. The applications include home control, hypermedia, office automation, digital photography , collaborative meeting/classrooms, public access, professional workstations, and medical record-keeping. Also, predictions are made for some of the underlying technologies such as User Interface Management Systems, remote control, flexible search, display devices, and touchscreens. 
