Reference-contexts: APPLICATIONS In the past decade improved user interfaces have opened up the door to the widespread use of word processors for writing, spreadsheet software in accounting, computer assisted design for engineering, and desktop publishing plus graphics in organizational communications <ref> (Shneiderman, 1987) </ref>. Here are some predictions about which applications will be similarly expanded in the next decade. The first group of applications have personal impact such as home control, public access information resources, and medical record keeping. <p> This field is still new , but already it shows promise of becoming one of the major software classes such as operating systems, compilers, or database management systems. Progress is needed in dealing more effectively with visually-oriented direct manipulation interfaces <ref> (Shneiderman, 1987) </ref> Remote control - do it there, do it then An exciting opportunity exists in designing remote control mechanisms. The remoteness may be in space, that is, controlling equipment at different locations, or it may be remoteness in time, controlling equipment operations at future times.
